Colombian Stocks: Bolsa de Valores, Ecopetrol, Fabricato

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-06-23T20:54:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/colombian-stocks-bolsa-de-valores-ecopetrol-fabricato.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are at 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.4 percent to 14,214.98 while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.5 percent to 1,712.98.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia (BVC)  SA, the operator of
Colombia’s main stock exchange, rose 1 percent, the most in
three weeks, to 41.8 pesos after Peru President-elect Ollanta
Humala said his policies won’t jeopardize the region’s fastest
growing economy. Peru’s change of government won’t affect the
development of capital markets, Francis Stenning, head of Bolsa
de Valores de Lima SA, operator of Peru’s main securities
exchange, told reporters. BVC shareholders decided June 16 to
postpone a vote on a planned merger with Peru’s BVL until the
Humala administration has a chance to review the planned merger.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL CB), Colombia’s largest oil company,
fell 0.8 percent to 3,775 pesos, the lowest since May 9. Oil
tumbled in New York, erasing its gains for the year, after the
 International Energy Agency  said its members would release crude
from strategic reserves.  Fabricato SA (FABRI CB), Colombia’s biggest textile maker,
fell 2.4 percent, the most in two weeks, to 61 pesos after U.S.
 House Republicans  postponed yesterday plans to consider
legislation that would implement free-trade accords with  South
Korea , Colombia and Panama.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
